article.description: Jill Young came off the bench to score a game-high 23 points, including a tiebreaking 3-pointer with 5:12 left, to lift South Dakota State (No. 16 ESPN/USA Today, No. 17 AP) past Oral Roberts 71-64 in the regular-season finale for both teams.
article.headline: Young scores 23 off bench as Jackrabbits win 14th straight game
article.linkText: S. Dakota St. repeats as Summit League champ
article.story:
TULSA, Okla. -- Jill Young came off the bench to score a game-high 23 points, including a tiebreaking 3-pointer with 5:12 left, to lift South Dakota State (No. 16 ESPN/USA Today, No. 17 AP) past Oral Roberts 71-64 in the regular-season finale for both teams on Monday night.

South Dakota State (28-2, 17-1) clinched its second consecutive Summit League title and extended its winning streak to 14 games.

Mariana Camargo led Oral Roberts (13-16, 6-12) with 15 points.

Young's seventh 3-pointer, a season high for the Jackrabbits, snapped a 52-52 tie and began a decisive 7-0 run. South Dakota State held the game's biggest lead at 62-54 after Maria Boever's two free throws with 1:41 left.

The Golden Eagles cut their deficit to 67-64 on Crystal Turner's layup with 33 seconds left, but South Dakota State held on as Kristin Rotert and Young combined to go 4-for-4 from the free-throw line in the final 31 seconds.
